Male macroptera. Colour and structure generally similar to female but paler and smaller. Antennal segments I–II pale; III–IX pale-yellow, V–IX paler (
Fig. 8
); ocellar triangle yellow; all legs pale (except coxae of mid and hind legs). Abdominal tergite I with two longitudinal ridges (
Fig. 5
), tergites without tubercles; tergite IX without claspers and stout curved setae but with two pairs of lateral setae of which the posterior pair is longer (
Fig. 6
). Sternite VII without sub-median accessory setae.

